t Soup  \n2nd Place вҖ“\u202fPumpkin and Shrimp Ceviche  \n3rd Place вҖ“\u202fButternut Squash Coleslaw  \nRunnerвҖ‘Up вҖ“\u202fAirвҖ‘Fried Pumpkin Shakarpara  \nRunnerвҖ‘Up вҖ“\u202fChocolate Squash Mousse  \nRunnerвҖ‘Up вҖ“\u202fPumpkin Falafel  \nRunnerвҖ‘Up вҖ“\u202fPumpkin Campfire Bars  \nRunnerвҖ‘Up вҖ“\u202fPumpkin Herb Rolls  \nRunnerвҖ‘Up вҖ“\u202fSpiced Pistachio Pumpkin Bread  \nRunnerвҖ‘Up вҖ“\u202fSweet Potato and Butternut Ravioli  \nMost Innovative вҖ“\u202fHerbed Pumpkin Flatbread\n</result>', include_extracted_content_only_once=False, metadata=None, include_in_memory=False), ActionResult(is_done=False, success=None, error=None, attachments=None, long_term_memory='Data written to file todo.md successfully.', extracted_content='Data written to file todo.md successfully.', include_extracted_content_only_once=False, metadata=None, include_in_memory=False), ActionResult(is_done=False, success=None, error=None, attachments=None, long_term_memory="Input 'Taste of Home contest winners prize' into element 10.", extracted_content="Input 'Taste of Home contest winners prize' into element 10.", include_extracted_content_only_once=False, metadata={'input_x': 778.6640625, 'input_y': 38.0}, include_in_memory=False), ActionResult(is_done=False, success=None, error=None, attachments=None, long_term_memory=None, extracted_content='Clicked element', include_extracted_content_only_once=False, metadata={'click_x': 916.1640625, 'click_y': 38.0, 'new_tab_opened': False}, include_in_memory=False), ActionResult(is_done=False, success=None, error=None, attachments=None, long_term_memory=None, extracted_content='Clicked element', include_extracted_content_only_once=False, metadata={'click_x': 770.6640625, 'click_y': 631, 'new_tab_opened': False}, include_in_memory=False), ActionResult(is_done=False, success=None, error=None, attachments=None, long_term_memory='Extracted content from https://www.tasteofhome.com/collection/5-ingredient-contest-winners/ for query: List all prize details mentioned on this page, including prize names and any associated descriptions.\nContent saved to file system: Extracted content saved to file extracted_content_0.md successfully. and displayed in <read_state>.', extracted_content='<url>\nhttps://www.tasteofhome.com/collection/5-ingredient-contest-winners/\n</url>\n<query>\nList all prize details mentioned on this page, including prize names and any associated descriptions.\n</query>\n<result>\nGrand Prize: **Feta Peach Salad**  \nDescription: вҖңThis refreshing, fiveвҖ‘ingredient side salad is a perfect way to celebrate the peach harvest. Incorporate it into your weekend brunch menu to introduce an explosion of color, freshness and flavor.вҖқ вҖ“ Rebecca Etienne  \n\n1st Place: **Fig Balsamic Walnut Flatbread**  \nDescription: вҖңWith sweet figs, tangy balsamic and rich goat cheese, this is one of my favorite flatbread recipes. ItвҖҷs also delicious with arugula and caramelized onions. I reach for it often when I host a special event or have friends over for dinner. You can use any storeвҖ‘bought flatbread or pizza dough.вҖқ вҖ“ Rebekah Ranes  \n\n2nd Place: **Easy Pesto Risotto with SunвҖ‘Dried Tomatoes**  \nDescription: вҖңI love this recipe because the pressure cooker does the work for you. IвҖҷm able to make the rest of my meal while the rice is cooking. Be sure to use arborio rice with this recipe.вҖқ вҖ“ Carrie Dault  \n\n3rd Place: **Sushi Squares**  \nDescription: вҖңWhen I was pregnant with my last child, the only thing I wanted was sushiвҖ”but pregnant people arenвҖҷt supposed to eat raw seafood. This simple yet delicious recipe is a safe way to satisfy a sushi craving. Add a thinly sliced jalapeno garnish to take this appetizer over the top.вҖқ вҖ“ Lizzy Richtig  \n\nRunnerвҖ‘Up: **Chocolate Peanut Butter Candy Crunch**  \nDescription: вҖңIf you love chocolate and peanut butter, youвҖҷll love this easy candy recipe! Anyone whoвҖҷs ever tried it wants me to share it with them. Serve it straight from the refrigerator or at room temperature.вҖқ вҖ“ Pat Parsons  \n\nRunnerвҖ‘Up: **Garlic Parmesan Smashed Potatoes**  \nDescription: вҖңPotatoes are one of our favorite side dishes. These potatoes take a little effort, but you can save time by boiling them ahead of time. The night you want them for dinner, just crisp them up with garlic and Parmesan cheese.вҖқ вҖ“ Donna Gribbins  \n\nRunnerвҖ‘Up: **Hoisin Chicken Wonton Cups**  \nDescription: вҖңThis is an easier take on the sesame chicken wonton tacos from ApplebeeвҖҷs. I made these recently for the big game and they were the star of the buffet! I toasted the wonton cups the day before to make assembly even faster on game day.вҖқ вҖ“ Anne Ormond  \n\nRunnerвҖ‘Up: **Mini Bagel Eggs Benedict**  \nDescription: вҖңWhy not make eggs Benedict with mini bagels instead of English muffins? The bagels soak up all the yummy hollandaise sauce. Garnish with a bit of thinly sliced green onions or chives for a delicious breakfast.вҖқ вҖ“ Theresa Ravencraft  \n\nRunnerвҖ‘Up: **Pesto Parmesan Tilapia**  \nDescription: вҖңThis is a delicious fish dinner that requires just three ingredients! Prepared pesto sauce flavors mild tilapia fillets to make a gourmet dinner any night of the week. Use homemade pesto sauce if you prefer. This also works well on any firmвҖ‘textured white fish.вҖқ вҖ“ Trisha Kruse  \n\nRunnerвҖ‘Up: **Saucy Maple Brussels Sprouts**  \nDescription: вҖңI like to toss ovenвҖ‘roasted Brussels sprouts with a mixture of maple syrup and mayo for a delicious side dish. They taste so good that even kids ask for seconds!вҖқ вҖ“ DonnaMarie Ryan  \n\nRunnerвҖ‘Up: **Scalloped Butternut Squash**  \nDescription: вҖңNot only is this winning recipe delicious, it has just five hardworking ingredients. I make it at least once a month and receive nothing but compliments every time. If you donвҖҷt have heavy cream, you can substitute halfвҖ‘andвҖ‘half or whole milk.вҖқ вҖ“ Dee James  \n\nRunnerвҖ‘Up: **Stuffed Olive Spread**  \nDesc